radiographic_examinations.findings: Mildly dilated (7-8 mm) appendix associated with moderate periappendiceal stranding and fluid. No drainable fluid collection or extraluminal gas. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, and rectum all within normal limits with no focal lesions. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No evidence of abdominal aortic aneurysm.
